<br>
Please excuse the tone of this post, but I find myself having to disprove this particular out-of-date rumor at least once a week.<br>
<br>
There is, and there has never been a minimum delay on a hasted weapon. There is a max haste cap, which is 100% and is only breakable by the two bard songs that stack with other item/spell haste effects (other bard hastes do not stack)<br>
<br>
The reason that people thought there was a minimum delay on haste was because back in the old days, the minimum delay you could get using the fastest weapon in the game (which were at that time, monk fists) was 10.<br>
<br>
However, these days, the minimum delay on a weapon can be much much lower.<br>
<br>
Try it. Parse a log of a Revultant Whip from hate at 100% haste. You will see that it attacks more than once per second, thus putting the delay below 10.<br>
<br>
Sorry, but the min delay thing is a false rumor. <p>--<br>
