<br>
Cleric epic = manaless rez, very useful<br>
Chanter epic = manaless instant haste, very useful<br>
Bard epic = increased song effectiveness, very useful<br>
Wizard epic = mana regen and rune, very useful<br>
Monk epic = song haste and stat boosts, somewhat useful<br>
Shaman epic = manaless DoT, somewhat useful<br>
Druid epic = manaless DoT, somewhat useful<br>
Necro epic = manaless snare DoT, somewhat useful<br>
Mage epic = uber pet, somewhat useful<br>
SK epic = Life Tap, somewhat useful<br>
Ranger epics = haste, almost useless; slow, almost useless<br>
Rogue epic = haste, almost useless<br>
Warrior epic = haste?, not really useful<br>
Pally epic = /shrug, don't even know what it does<br>
<br>
Any epic that doesn't have a unique effect is almost useless.<br>
<br>
Cleric epic should have rez effects removed...<br>
Chanter epic is fine the way it is...<br>
Bard epic shouldn't be as hard as it is to obtain...<br>
Wizard epic is fine the way it is...<br>
Shaman epic shouldn't be a dot, it should be a buff like the chanter epic, make it like avatar or something without the component...<br>
Monk epic needs cooler graphics :P<br>
Druid epic is entirely too easy and should be changed to a SoE type click effect that can be cast indoors...<br>
Necro epic should be a DieHard battery and make their twitching twice as effective since that is all they are good for on raids anyway... (kidding)<br>
Mage epic is fine the way it is, maybe a little too difficult...<br>
SK epic should be a self buff that increases taunt by 20 percent or something similar.<br>
Ranger epics should be harder to obtain but should have the opposite effect as the SK epic, they should have an effect of lessening aggro.<br>
Rogue epic should have a chance for an extra backstab (yes triple backstab)<br>
Warrior epic should be a sheild that can be worn while wielding a 2hander. (not an effect but a unique feature, no other shields should have this quality)... give the shield 300hps and other godly stats that make a meatshield a good meatshield.<br>
Pally epic should um, make the pally less of a gimp... I can't come up with anything here (again joking).  Maybe a process that is a unresistable stun even to unstunnable mobs like giants and such.<br>
<br>
They all need improvement actually.  Add to the quests and update the stats to be on par with SoL uber gear.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/utarskxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TarskXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Xev Councillor</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#330000>(5/16/02 8:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which &quot;Epic&quot; weapon should VI improve?</span><hr size=1> hehe, I apologize again for the tone of my post. Was actually the second time this week that I had to correct someone on the minimum delay thing, and I find myself doing it regularly on Everlore.<br>
<br>
I'll dig out a log sometime soon and post it.. But yeah, triple attack does complicate things a little.<br>
<br>
What do you mean about double attacks following the 1 second delay rule?<br>
<br>
As far as I am aware what happens is this (on your primary hand):<br>
<br>
When your (hasted) weapon timer recycles you make a double attack check. I believe the formula for this is:<br>
<br>
(DA Skill+lvl)/600<br>
<br>
If that check is successfull, you double attack. If not, you don't. I wasn't aware there was anything more to it than that? =) <br>
